From: "K. Y. Srinivasan" <kys@microsoft.com>
Date: Fri, 10 Aug 2018 23:06:07 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Tools: hv: Fix a bug in the key delete code
References: bnc#1012382
Patch-mainline: 4.4.158
Git-commit: 86503bd35dec0ce363e9fdbf5299927422ed3899

commit 86503bd35dec0ce363e9fdbf5299927422ed3899 upstream.

Fix a bug in the key delete code - the num_records range
from 0 to num_records-1.

Signed-off-by: K. Y. Srinivasan <kys@microsoft.com>
Reported-by: David Binderman <dcb314@hotmail.com>
Cc: <stable@vger.kernel.org>
Reviewed-by: Michael Kelley <mikelley@microsoft.com>
Signed-off-by: Greg Kroah-Hartman <gregkh@linuxfoundation.org>
Signed-off-by: Jiri Slaby <jslaby@suse.cz>
---
 tools/hv/hv_kvp_daemon.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/tools/hv/hv_kvp_daemon.c b/tools/hv/hv_kvp_daemon.c
index 60a94b3e532e..177480066816 100644
--- a/tools/hv/hv_kvp_daemon.c
+++ b/tools/hv/hv_kvp_daemon.c
@@ -286,7 +286,7 @@ static int kvp_key_delete(int pool, const __u8 *key, int key_size)
 		 * Found a match; just move the remaining
 		 * entries up.
 		 */
-		if (i == num_records) {
+		if (i == (num_records - 1)) {
 			kvp_file_info[pool].num_records--;
 			kvp_update_file(pool);
 			return 0;
